    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>and <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
